Common syndromes in family medicine. Risk groups, screening methods in family practice. Prevention and health promotion in family practice. Consultation in family practice, training of consultation skills. Management of problems in different age and gender groups. Community approach in family practice. Evidence-based approach in family practice.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To introduce the management of different age and gender groups in primary health care, to elaborate communication skills with patients. To expand students'  understanding of an influence of a community and a family to an individual, and how to effectively prevent illnesses in a primary health care. To introduce the principles management of chronically ill patients in individual level but also in the level of the whole family.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After the course the student : 
- knows the most important differential diagnosis principles in family practice;
- is able to interpret the results of the most important laboratory analysis and other investigations used in family practice;
- knows to describe most important prevention methods in family practice;
- knows the core principles o f the management of the chronically ill patient;
- pharmacotherapy is able to assess the appropriateness of a particular patient;
- knows the principles of palliative care;
- is able to document clinically at general practitioner level and to plan outpatient admissions.
